.TH hsh 1 "February 2026" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command language interpreter.

The shell displays a prompt and waits for the user to type a command.
Command lines are simple and contain only one word.
No arguments are supported.

The shell:
.TP
\(bu displays a prompt
.TP
\(bu executes commands without arguments
.TP
\(bu handles errors
.TP
\(bu handles EOF (Ctrl+D)
.TP
\(bu uses execve to execute programs

If the executable cannot be found, an error message is printed
and the prompt is displayed again.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns 0 on success.
If execve fails, the child process exits with status 127.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell passes the environment to execve.

